<html extends="DocPage">
<head title="Layers view"/>

<body>
   <div id="content">
      <div id="pageContent" exec="server">
         <h2>Layers view</h2>
           Shows active layers of the last run/debug program, or all available layers, or available layers loaded in this session.
           <p>
           <img style="margin:0px auto;display:block" src="../images/activeInactiveLayers.png" alt="Active layers"/>
           <br>
           Here are the inactive layers:
           <p>
           <img style="margin:0px auto;display:block" src="../images/inactiveLayersJS.png" alt="Inactive layers"/>
           <br>
         <h2>Layers organized by process or runtime</h2>
          Some layers are tied to a specific process or runtime. Other layers inherit dependencies from the layers they extend. StrataCode organizes layers based on these process/runtime constraints. The layers view helps you understand which layers are available where.
          <p>
          Here are the active layers in the server process of the doc application running in client/server mode:
           <p>
           <img style="margin:0px auto;display:block" src="../images/layersViewRuntimes.png" alt="Layers view runtimes"/>
           <p>
           Here are the active layers in the JS runtime for the same application:
           <p>
           <img style="margin:0px auto;display:block" src="../images/activeLayersJS.png" alt="Client layers"/>
           <br>

         <h2>Layers organized by type</h2>
         The layer definition file can contain metadata to identify the type of code in that particular layer.  
         <p>
         Here are the available framework layers that you can use with the Java server process:
           <img style="margin:0px auto;display:block" src="../images/layersViewTypes.png" alt="Layers view runtimes"/>
           <p>
         <h2>Dynamic layers</h2>
         A dynamic layer has a green icon in the layers view:
           <img style="vertical-align:middle" src="../images/dynLayersView.png" alt="Dynamic layers view"/>
           <p>

         <a href="ideOverview.html">Back to IDE overview</a>

      </div>
   </div>
</body>
</html>
